MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9e7c527a6f66a8c49a6fab10a94681fc, type: 3}
  m_Name: Day1Morning
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  sequenceId: 
  lines:
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Morning, Andy. Welcome to another beautiful day on the SUNSET16. You\u2019ve
      been assigned maintenance on Section C-12 of the ship again for the foreseeable
      future. Wire duty. It\u2019s up your alley as a Technician. Your efficiency
      ratings have been stellar these past 5 years. DOLOS is pleased."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "It\u2019s what I\u2019m here for."
      nextLineIndex: 1
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Exactly. Now, need a refresher on wiring protocols, or are you good on
      that front?
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "A refresher wouldn\u2019t hurt."
      nextLineIndex: 2
    - choiceText: "I\u2019m good. Red to red, don\u2019t cross the streams. Simple."
      nextLineIndex: 3
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "It\u2019s the standard grid-based alignment. Connect the correctly coloured
      endpoints without allowing the paths to cross. Watch out for weird edge cases.
      Don\u2019t improvise the wiring."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: Affirmative.
      nextLineIndex: 4
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Heh. You\u2019ve done this a thousand times. Still, check the manual whenever
      you need to. Always good to keep your mind sharp."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices: []
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Any other questions before you start? My shift at Section M-67 doesn\u2019t
      begin for another 20."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices: []
